text: Enlil-Nasir II was the king of Assyria from 1420 BC to 1414 BC. The brother of Ashur-nadin-ahhe I, he seized the throne in a successful coup. ==References== * Category:1414 BC deaths Category:15th-century BC Assyrian kings Category:Assyrian kings Category:Leaders who took power by coup Category:Year of birth unknown Category:15th-century BC rulers
title: Enlil-Nasir II
